message.content:
cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing techniques (neural networks, sentiment analysis) applied to social media data (Facebook posts and comments).
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also a likely category as the paper focuses on analyzing user reactions to posts on social media platforms.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper deals with predicting the distribution of reactions to posts, which can be seen as a form of information retrieval.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses neural network architectures to predict the reactions to posts.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with analyzing user behavior on social media platforms, which has implications for society and privacy.
